modules.name: Control.Arrow
modules.comments: Type classes and standard instances for Arrows.

declarations.comments:
The `Arrow` type class combines the operations of a `Category` with those of
a `Strong` profunctor.
declarations.title: Arrow

declarations.comments: Arrows with a monoidal operation on morphisms
declarations.title: ArrowPlus

declarations.comments:
`Cokleisli` gives an `Arrow` instance for the Co-Kleisli category of a `Comonad`.

Composition is defined using `=>=` with `extract` as the identity morhism.
declarations.title: Cokleisli

declarations.comments:
`Kleisli` gives an `Arrow` instance for the Kleisli category of a `Monad`.

Composition is defined using `>=>` with `return` as the identity morhism.
declarations.title: Kleisli

modules.name: Control.Arrow.Static
modules.comments: The `Static` arrow transformer for an `Applicative` functor.

declarations.comments: `Static` gives an `Arrow` instance for the static arrows of an `Applicative` functor.
declarations.title: Static
